<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Omoyele-Sowore1-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&#038;ssl=1" alt="We are deeply concerned Sowore re-detained ― U.S. State Dept" align="left" style="margin: 0 20px 20px 0;max-width:100%" data-recalc-dims="1" /> By Rasheed Sobowale The United States Bureau of Democracy, Human Rights, and Labor has joined voices to express discontent at Nigeria’s Department State Security (DSS) action to rearrest Omoyele Sowore after he was released less than 24 hours. Sowore, the convener of the RevelotionNow Movement was rearrested by the security agency in the Federal High Court, Abuja premises following the adjournment of theur trial till February 11, 2019 by the sitting judge, Justice Ijeoma Ojukwu. Continue reading We are deeply concerned Sowore re-detained ― U.S. State Dept at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard